original_title: First giant panda cub of 2025 born at panda base in SW China's Sichuan
article_summary: First Giant Panda Cub of 2025 Born at Sichuan Base in China (June 26, 2025) - The China Conservation and Research Center for the Giant Panda welcomed the year's first giant panda cub in captivity at the Shenshuping Base in Sichuan Province. The cub was born to first-time mother Linlang following a successful natural mating with male panda Yaxing in early March. Both mother and cub are in good health.</s>
